Pour the @water for the rice{200%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
lid.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{100%g} and @salt{0.25%tsp}, then bring to the boil. Once boiling,
turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve the @mangetout{80%g} widthways.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British Pork Mince{240%g} and @sliced mushrooms{80%g}. Fry until
the mince and mushrooms have browned, ~{6-7%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up
the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked
> when no longer pink in the middle.

While the mince and mushrooms cook, trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{}
to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Pop the ribbons into a #medium bowl{}. Add the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and
@sugar for the pickle{1%tsp}. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and mix together. Set
your carrot pickle aside.

Once the mince has cooked, add the mangetout, garlic and @gochujang paste{50%g} to
the pan. Stir-fry until the veg starts to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the @honey{15%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml} and @water for the sauce{50%ml}. Reduce
the heat and simmer until the liquid has reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Stir through the @BBQ sauce{32%g}, then remove from the heat.

Fluff the rice up with a #fork{} and share it out between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the Korean style BBQ pork and serve the carrot pickle on the side.

Enjoy!